4 3-A. Annual base compensation. "Annual base compensation" means a member's
5 gross compensation, based upon amounts reported by the member's employer on the
6 member's earnable compensation in the previous year's federal wage and tax statement,
7 year that is used the first day of each April for setting the amount of coverage prior to
8 retirement for participants in the group life insurance program administered by the board,
9 except that, in a member's first year of hire or for a participant who is not a member, "annual
10 base compensation" means the expected annual earnable compensation of a participant as
11 reported by the participant's employer in a manner specified by the chief executive officer.
12 SUMMARY
1133 This bill changes the source of information used to set group life insurance coverage
1144 levels under the Maine Public Employees Retirement System.
